Enum LdapResultCode

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<LdapResultCode>
      • com.radiantlogic.iddm.ldap.LdapResultCode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    StatusCode, Serializable, Comparable<LdapResultCode>

    public enum LdapResultCode
extends Enum<LdapResultCode>
implements StatusCode
    Enumeration of LDAP result codes based on RFC 4511.

    This enum provides standard LDAP result codes with their corresponding integer values and string representations as defined in RFC 4511 Section 4.1.9.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • SUCCESS

        public static final LdapResultCode SUCCESS
        Indicates the successful completion of an operation.

      • OPERATIONS_ERROR

        public static final LdapResultCode OPERATIONS_ERROR
        Indicates that the operation is not properly sequenced with relation to other operations (of same or different type). For example:
        • Client attempts to StartTLS [RFC4346] while there are other uncompleted operations or if a TLS layer was already installed.
        • Client sends a request that is only allowed for authenticated clients.
        • Client sends any request on a connection that is actively processing a bind.

        This result code should not be used for internal server errors; in that case, use OTHER (80) instead.

      • NO_SUCH_OBJECT

        public static final LdapResultCode NO_SUCH_OBJECT
        Indicates that the object does not exist in the DIT.

      • INVALID_CREDENTIALS

        public static final LdapResultCode INVALID_CREDENTIALS
        Indicates that the provided credentials (e.g., the user's name and password) are invalid.

      • INSUFFICIENT_ACCESS_RIGHTS

        public static final LdapResultCode INSUFFICIENT_ACCESS_RIGHTS
        Indicates that the client does not have sufficient access rights to perform the operation.

      • UNAVAILABLE

        public static final LdapResultCode UNAVAILABLE
        Indicates that the server or a subsystem needed to process the request is currently not available to process the requested operation.

      • OTHER

        public static final LdapResultCode OTHER
        Indicates the server has encountered an internal error. Use when a problem occurs for which none of the other result codes is more appropriate.
